Reason:
The bug occurs because `nd->last_type` is incorrectly set to `LAST_NORM` instead of `LAST_BIND` when handling autofs direct mounts. This incorrect type leads to an invalid pointer being freed during the open operation, specifically when `nd.last.name` is accessed, resulting in potential memory management issues.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
